headline: Why Copart Stock Spiked 9% Today
summary: In a press release last night that topped out at 169 words (a third of which were just telling investors how to tune in for its earnings conference call), Copart efficiently explained to investors how it met analyst forecasts for fiscal Q1 2025 earnings and beat expectations for revenues.  Copart stock is up 8.9% through 10:30 a.m. ET in response.  Copart grew its revenues 12% year over year in Q1 to $1.15 billion, about $50 million more than Wall Street's forecast.
